        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 12:52PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 1252 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Dawsonville, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dahlonega, Dawsonville, Dougherty, Silver City, Hollis Lathem
Reservoir, Auraria, Hightower, War Hill Park, and McKee.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
